  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "This is a set of 18th-century compound pulley blocks (*katrollen*) made by the Amsterdam instrument makers **J. Kampman and Jean Pelletier**, used to demonstrate mechanical advantage through block-and-tackle pulley systems. The apparatus retains its **original cord** — a rare survival of organic material on an 18th-century scientific instrument. It is one of two pulley demonstrations by Kampman & Pelletier in the Teylers collection (the other being FK 0018, a pulley stand), and forms part of a larger suite of Newtonian mechanics apparatus based on designs by **Willem Jacob 's Gravesande** (1688–1742).",
